-CAROLINE:
APPROACHING 100 FEET.

11:59.806 --> 12:01.982
HEY, NEELY, WHY DON'T YOU
HOLD OUT THERE FOR A BIT OKAY?

12:02.112 --> 12:03.157
LET SAM CHECK YOU OUT.

12:04.332 --> 12:05.463
-SAM: EVERYTHING LOOKS GOOD.

12:05.594 --> 12:07.030
I'LL WAIT FOR NEELY HERE.

12:07.161 --> 12:08.684
HEY, NEELY, REMEMBER
TO WATCH YOUR LEVELS.

12:08.815 --> 12:10.207
-NEELY: I'LL BRING YOU
A SOUVENIR FROM THE BOTTOM.

12:12.688 --> 12:14.472
I'M AT 200 FEET.

12:14.603 --> 12:16.039
-SOUNDS LIKE THE
MIX IS PRETTY GOOD.

12:16.170 --> 12:20.783
-NEELY: HELIUM'S AT 50,
NITROGEN 34, OXYGEN 16.

12:20.914 --> 12:22.742
-SAM: HOW'S YOUR BODY TEMP?
-NEELY: PERFECT.

12:23.699 --> 12:25.266
-SAM: GOOD, LET'S KEEP GOING.

12:26.093 --> 12:27.703
-NEELY: 300 FEET.

12:27.834 --> 12:32.316
HELIUM 65%, NITROGEN
25, OXYGEN 10.

12:32.447 --> 12:34.492
TEMP'S GOOD.
[RADIO STATIC]

12:34.623 --> 12:37.887
[HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]
I'M APPROACHING AT 400.

12:38.758 --> 12:40.237
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

12:42.587 --> 12:43.850
-HEY, NEELY, ARE YOU OKAY?

12:43.980 --> 12:45.286
YOU'RE STARTING
TO SLUR YOUR WORDS.

12:45.895 --> 12:47.897
-SAM: NEELY, CHECK
YOUR NITROGEN LEVEL.

12:50.204 --> 12:54.643
-LOOK, A MANTA RAY.
COME HERE, COME HERE.

12:54.774 --> 12:56.471
[RADIO STATIC]
SWIM WITH ME, BABY.

12:56.601 --> 12:58.952
-SAM: NEELY, NEELY YOUR
NITROGEN LEVEL MUST BE TOO HIGH.

12:59.082 --> 13:00.301
START COMING UP.

13:00.431 --> 13:02.564
-NEELY: NO,
I LOVE IT DOWN HERE.

13:02.694 --> 13:04.348
-SAM, SAM,
I THINK SHE'S NARCED.

13:04.479 --> 13:06.786
-SAM: NEELY, LISTEN TO ME,
ONE OF YOUR VALVES

13:06.916 --> 13:08.962
MUST BE STUCK, YOUR
NITROGEN IS TOO HIGH.

13:09.092 --> 13:10.441
YOU'RE GETTING NARCED.

13:10.572 --> 13:12.356
NEELY, COME UP NOW, FOCUS.

13:12.487 --> 13:15.533
NEELY, SWIM UP,
60 FEET PER MINUTE.

13:16.665 --> 13:18.145
-NEELY, LISTEN TO ME, OKAY?

13:18.275 --> 13:20.234
I WANT YOU TO LISTEN TO MY
VOICE AND KICK YOUR FEET

13:20.364 --> 13:21.583
EVERY TIME I COUNT, ALL RIGHT?

13:22.497 --> 13:25.848
ONE, TWO, ONE, TWO,

13:26.588 --> 13:28.633
ONE, TWO.
-SAM: I SEE HER.

13:28.764 --> 13:31.941
-CAROLINE:
ONE, TWO, ONE, TWO.

13:32.594 --> 13:33.813
ONE, TWO.

13:33.943 --> 13:35.336
-SAM: NEELY, IT'S
OKAY, I GOT YA.

13:35.858 --> 13:37.338
COME ON, WE'RE GONNA
SWIM UP TOGETHER.

13:39.383 --> 13:40.602
[RADIO STATIC]

13:42.169 --> 13:44.127
HERE WE GO, THAT'S IT.

13:59.751 --> 14:00.927
-THAT WAS WILD.

14:02.058 --> 14:03.712
NOW I KNOW WHY I QUIT
DRINKING. [LAUGHS]

14:03.843 --> 14:05.583
-NEELY, I AM SO SORRY.

14:05.714 --> 14:07.803
-OH, DON'T BE, THAT'S
WHY WE HAD TO TEST IT.

14:07.934 --> 14:09.805
-THE VALVE MUST'VE JAMMED.

14:13.461 --> 14:15.985
-WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING THAT
NITROGEN DISSIPATES QUICKLY.

14:16.116 --> 14:17.247
-NEELY: YEAH.

14:18.814 --> 14:22.426
-HEY, THAT JET'S
FLYING PRETTY LOW.

14:22.557 --> 14:25.168
[ENGINE ROARING]

14:26.082 --> 14:27.649
-I THINK HE'S IN TROUBLE.

14:27.779 --> 14:30.217
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

14:31.609 --> 14:32.959
-OH, LOOK, HE'S EJECTED!

14:40.096 --> 14:41.619
-SAM: HE'S GONNA HIT THE
WATER, WE'VE GOTTA GET HIM.

14:41.750 --> 14:42.620
LET'S GO.

14:59.899 --> 15:01.378
THERE HE IS! NEELY, SLOW DOWN.

15:26.012 --> 15:27.578
-CAROLINE: HE'S UNCONSCIOUS.

15:27.709 --> 15:28.971
LET'S GET HIM TO THE BOAT.

15:42.637 --> 15:43.768
-NEELY: HE'S ALIVE.

15:46.249 --> 15:47.511
-HE'S NOT BREATHING.

15:55.693 --> 15:58.000
[COUGHING]

15:58.131 --> 15:59.219
-NEELY: I'M GONNA
MAKE THE CALL.

16:00.437 --> 16:02.744
-YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.
WE'RE LIFEGUARDS.

16:06.487 --> 16:08.663
-KMF 295--

16:08.793 --> 16:10.491
-NO, DON'T DO THAT.
-NEELY: FROM DIVER 143.

16:13.407 --> 16:15.017
-SORRY, MA'AM, I'VE
RADIOED MY POSITION

16:15.148 --> 16:17.063
ON SECURE FREQUENCY
BEFORE I EJECTED.

16:17.715 --> 16:19.239
THERE WILL BE A RESCUE
TEAM HERE SHORTLY.

16:20.022 --> 16:21.284
IN THE MEAN TIME,
I NEED TO RECOVER

16:21.415 --> 16:23.199
MY EJECTION SEAT IMMEDIATELY.

16:23.330 --> 16:25.027
-WAIT A SECOND,
WHY DON'T WE JUST WAIT

16:25.158 --> 16:26.550
FOR YOUR RESCUE TEAM?

16:26.681 --> 16:28.770
-BY THAT TIME ALL OCEAN
LIFE COULD BE DESTROYED.

16:32.295 --> 16:33.601
-WHAT KIND OF
MISSION WERE YOU ON?

16:36.169 --> 16:37.561
-YOU SAVED MY LIFE SO
I'M GOING TO TELL YOU,

16:37.692 --> 16:39.476
BUT THIS IS
CLASSIFIED TOP SECRET.

16:40.303 --> 16:43.306
I WAS TRANSPORTING
A DEADLY STRAIN OF CHOLERA

16:43.437 --> 16:45.091
THAT WAS RECOVERED
FROM A TERRORIST GROUP.

16:45.961 --> 16:49.095
THEY INTENDED TO POISON
A MAJOR CITY'S WATER SUPPLY.

16:49.617 --> 16:51.749
-WELL, IT MUST BE
CONTAINED IN SOMETHING.

16:51.880 --> 16:54.056
-YES, MA'AM, BUT IT
WAS RIGGED WITH A TIMER.

16:54.187 --> 16:57.146
IF IT WAS TRIGGERED ON IMPACT,
WE'D HAVE LESS THAN AN HOUR

16:57.277 --> 16:59.018
TO RECOVER IT.

16:59.148 --> 17:01.020
-NOW, WAIT A SECOND, THAT'S
OVER 400 FEET TO THE BOTTOM.

17:01.150 --> 17:04.153
-LOOK, I CAN DIVE THAT DEEP
IF SAM CAN FIX THE VALVE.

17:04.284 --> 17:07.156
-WELL, I CAN TRY,
BUT I DON'T KNOW IF IT CAN HOLD

17:07.287 --> 17:08.549
THAT KIND OF DEPTH.

17:08.679 --> 17:10.203
-THERE'S ONLY ONE
WAY TO FIND OUT.

17:10.333 --> 17:11.508
-NO, NO, NO, WAIT A SECOND,
I THINK WE SHOULD WAIT

17:11.638 --> 17:13.075
FOR THE RESCUE TEAM,
I REALLY DO.

17:13.205 --> 17:14.945
NEELY, YOU'VE ALREADY
HAD ONE CLOSE CALL.

17:15.077 --> 17:16.165
-IF YOU SHOW ME HOW TO USE THE
GEAR AND I'LL MAKE THE DIVE.

17:16.296 --> 17:17.471
-NO, NO, NO, I CAN DO IT.

17:17.601 --> 17:18.993
SAM, GO FIX IT.

17:19.125 --> 17:20.734
WHAT DOES THE
CANISTER LOOK LIKE?

17:21.431 --> 17:23.390
-IT'S CLEAR, YOU
CAN SEE THE BACTERIA

17:23.520 --> 17:24.739
AND AN EXPLOSIVE CHARGE.

17:24.868 --> 17:26.045
EVERYTHING'S INSIDE OF IT.

17:26.175 --> 17:28.089
-WAIT A SECOND,
BACTERIA AND EXPLOSIVES?

17:28.221 --> 17:30.266
-I DON'T KNOW, WHAT
DO I DO WHEN I FIND IT?

17:30.397 --> 17:32.355
-THE TIMER'S BEEN
TRIGGERED, YOU NEED TO USE

17:32.486 --> 17:36.968
A DISABLE CODE,
IT'S 099 ALPHA 247.

17:37.099 --> 17:38.709
-OKAY, TELL ME AGAIN
WHEN I FIND IT, ALL RIGHT?

17:38.840 --> 17:39.841
OKAY.

17:43.975 --> 17:45.412
-WHAT HAPPENS IF
THIS THING GOES OFF?

17:45.542 --> 17:46.674
WHAT HAPPENS TO NEELY?

17:47.718 --> 17:48.763
-SHE WOULD BE INFECTED.

18:13.788 --> 18:15.311
-SAM: SHE'S AT 300 FEET.

18:16.530 --> 18:17.618
-SHE'S AT 300 FEET.

18:18.314 --> 18:19.620
-SAM: NEELY, CAN YOU
SEE THE BOTTOM YET?

18:20.229 --> 18:22.144
-NEELY: ABOUT 30 FEET MORE.

18:22.797 --> 18:24.407
-DO YOU SEE THE EJECTION SEAT?

18:24.538 --> 18:26.801
-NEELY: NOT YET.
-NO, NOT YET.

18:29.195 --> 18:30.413
LET ME PUT THIS ON SPEAKER.

18:37.855 --> 18:39.335
-NEELY: I SEE IT.

18:40.467 --> 18:42.947
-GO TO THE BOX ATTACHED
TO THE RIGHT ARM REST.

18:53.132 --> 18:55.177
IS IT STILL THERE?
-NEELY: YES.

19:00.269 --> 19:03.620
-OPEN IT CAREFULLY. THERE'S
A LATCH ON EACH SIDE.

19:13.891 --> 19:15.502
[BEEPING]

19:15.632 --> 19:16.764
-NEELY: I SEE THE CANISTER.

19:18.679 --> 19:21.116
-QUINLIN: TURN THE UNIT TO
THE ROD WITH THE TIMER IN IT.

19:21.638 --> 19:22.770
-NEELY: I SEE THE TIMER.

19:25.512 --> 19:28.863
-HAS IT BEEN ACTIVATED?
ARE THE NUMBERS COUNTING DOWN?

19:28.993 --> 19:32.127
-YES. IT'S ALMOST
DOWN TO 11 MINUTES.

19:46.315 --> 19:51.146
-THE DISABLE CODE
IS 099 ALPHA 247.

19:51.277 --> 19:53.279
-NEELY: ALPHA, YOU MEAN A?

19:53.409 --> 19:57.457
-QUINLIN: YES. 099 A 247.

20:02.505 --> 20:03.593
-NEELY: IT'S NOT WORKING.

20:05.334 --> 20:06.988
-THAT'S ALL RIGHT,
TRY IT AGAIN.

20:14.343 --> 20:16.954
-NEELY: NOTHING,
IT STILL DOESN'T WORK.

20:17.607 --> 20:18.913
-LOOK, ARE YOU SURE
YOU HAVE THE RIGHT CODE?

20:19.043 --> 20:20.219
-YES, MA'AM, I'M POSITIVE.

20:20.871 --> 20:22.830
THE WATER PRESSURE MUST BE
AFFECTING THE MECHANISM.

20:22.960 --> 20:24.310
NEELY, CAN YOU HEAR ME?

20:24.440 --> 20:25.920
-YES.

20:26.050 --> 20:28.270
-YOU'LL HAVE TO BRING
IT UP TO THE SURFACE.

20:28.401 --> 20:30.141
WE'LL TRY
TO DISARM IT UP HERE.

20:30.881 --> 20:32.187
-SAM: NEELY, HOW
MUCH TIME IS LEFT?

20:32.318 --> 20:33.710
-NEELY: EIGHT MINUTES.

20:33.841 --> 20:35.712
-SAM: YOU CAN NEVER
DECOMPRESS IN TIME.

20:37.105 --> 20:38.585
-NEELY: OKAY, I'M STARTING UP.

20:38.715 --> 20:41.588
-SAM: NEELY, STOP AT 225,
I'LL MEET YOU THERE.

20:41.718 --> 20:43.851
CAROLINE, PUT ON YOUR
GEAR AND COME TO 100 FEET.

20:43.981 --> 20:45.809
I'LL PASS
THE CANISTER TO YOU.

20:58.431 --> 21:00.868
-I HOPE YOU APPRECIATE ALL
THE TROUBLE YOU PUT US THROUGH.

21:00.998 --> 21:02.217
-YOU SAVED MY LIFE, MA'AM.

21:02.348 --> 21:03.523
I APPRECIATE
EVERYTHING YOU'VE DONE

21:03.653 --> 21:05.046
AND EVERYTHING YOU'RE DOING.

21:05.176 --> 21:07.831
-WELL, GOOD. PLEASE
STOP CALLING ME "MA'AM."

21:18.712 --> 21:20.670
[BEEPING]

21:26.937 --> 21:28.025
-SAM: I GOT IT.

21:46.087 --> 21:48.219
CAREFUL WITH IT.
YOU GOT IT?

21:49.482 --> 21:52.136
-I GOT IT. MY GOD,
LOOK AT THIS THING.

22:06.499 --> 22:08.675
-NEELY: I HAVE TO STAY
DOWN A FEW MORE MINUTES. SAM?

22:08.805 --> 22:11.808
-SAM: ME, TOO. CAROLINE'S
TAKING THE CANISTER UP.

22:25.735 --> 22:27.824
OKAY, SHE'S ON THE
SURFACE. NEELY?

22:29.304 --> 22:30.305
-NEELY: I'M COMING UP.

22:52.414 --> 22:53.807
-SAM: I'M SURFACING.

22:57.811 --> 22:59.160
-QUINLIN: IT'S SHUTTING DOWN.
[BEEPS OFF]

23:01.249 --> 23:05.340
-KMF 295 FROM DIVER 143
REQUESTING EMERGENCY ASSISTANCE.

23:05.471 --> 23:08.517
-KMF 295, WHAT IS YOUR
LOCATION, CAROLINE.

23:09.953 --> 23:11.390
[GUNSHOTS FIRING]
[GASPING]

23:14.480 --> 23:17.308
CAROLINE? CAROLINE?

23:22.052 --> 23:22.966
-CAROLINE.

23:23.097 --> 23:24.577
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

23:24.707 --> 23:26.230
-I CAN'T ALLOW MY
MISSION TO BE COMPROMISED.

23:26.361 --> 23:27.710
I'M SORRY.

23:28.711 --> 23:31.018
[SCREAMING]

23:35.152 --> 23:36.980
-QUINLIN, WHAT THE
HELL ARE YOU DOING?

23:37.111 --> 23:38.460
-I'M DOING WHAT I HAVE TO DO.

23:38.591 --> 23:40.157
-PLEASE, YOU CAN'T
JUST LEAVE US LIKE THIS.

23:40.288 --> 23:43.465
-I WISH THERE WAS SOME
OTHER WAY. I'M SORRY.

23:44.335 --> 23:45.859
-QUINLIN, COME BACK.

23:53.214 --> 23:55.129
MY KNEE, IT MIGHT BE BROKEN.

24:00.787 --> 24:04.138
-DIVER 143, THIS IS BAYWATCH.
COME IN, CAROLINE.

24:04.268 --> 24:06.009
-WHAT'S GOING ON? IS
EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

24:06.140 --> 24:09.143
-I DON'T KNOW. CAROLINE
REQUESTED EMERGENCY ASSISTANCE

24:09.273 --> 24:11.885
BUT HER TRANSMISSION ENDED
BEFORE I COULD GET ANY DETAILS.

24:17.847 --> 24:20.197
-WHAT HAPPENED?
WHERE'S OUR BOAT?

24:20.328 --> 24:22.243
-THAT PILOT,
HE SHOT OUT THE RADIO.

24:22.765 --> 24:25.376
HE TOOK THE CANISTER, HE TOOK
THE BOAT, HE TOOK EVERYTHING.

24:25.507 --> 24:27.683
-HOW COULD HE LET US DROWN?
HE'S AN AIR FORCE PILOT.

24:28.336 --> 24:29.642
-LET'S HOPE
THAT'S WHAT HE IS.

24:29.772 --> 24:31.252
-NEELY: WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

24:31.382 --> 24:33.297
-IF HE'S A TERRORIST,
WE JUST HELPED RECOVER

24:33.428 --> 24:34.429
HIS WEAPON FOR HIM.

24:36.562 --> 24:38.607
-THESE MAJOR INCIDENTS
REPORTS, THEY'RE LIKE

24:38.738 --> 24:39.782
READING ACTION BOOKS.

24:39.913 --> 24:41.349
MITCH IS THE HERO IN THIS ONE.

24:41.480 --> 24:43.133
CAROLINE IN THIS ONE.

24:43.786 --> 24:45.484
I CAN'T WAIT TO START
LIFEGUARDING FOR REAL.

24:45.614 --> 24:47.094
WRITE THESE UP INSTEAD
OF FILING THEM.

24:47.224 --> 24:48.617
-WHAT'S GOING ON, YOU GUYS?

24:48.748 --> 24:49.966
-WELL, I'M WORRIED ABOUT
SAM, NEELY AND CAROLINE.

24:50.097 --> 24:51.620
-WHY? WHAT'S WRONG?

24:51.751 --> 24:54.188
-WELL, CAROLINE RADIOED IN,
SHE SOUNDED TENSE.

24:54.318 --> 24:55.972
THEN THERE WAS A LOUD
POP ON THE SIGNAL.

24:56.103 --> 24:58.279
I TRIED TO RAISE THEM AGAIN,
BUT THERE WAS NO RESPONSE.

24:58.409 --> 24:59.628
-DID YOU RADIO THE COAST GUARD?

24:59.759 --> 25:00.716
-YEAH, THEY'RE
DIVERTING A CUTTER

25:00.847 --> 25:01.804
TO THE LAST KNOWN DIVE AREA.

25:01.935 --> 25:03.458
-WE'LL HEAR SOMETHING SOON.

25:03.589 --> 25:05.286
I'M SURE IT'S JUST
A SHORT IN THE RADIO.

25:05.416 --> 25:07.854
HERE YOU GO, MANNY, SOME MORE
INCIDENT REPORTS TO FILE.

25:07.984 --> 25:09.116
-WHAT KIND OF RESCUE, MAN?

25:09.246 --> 25:10.073
-TAKE A LOOK.

25:10.813 --> 25:12.380
-WHAT KIND OF POP WAS THAT?

25:12.511 --> 25:14.556
-IT WAS LOUD LIKE A
GUNSHOT OR A RADIO SHORTING.

25:14.687 --> 25:16.297
-I'M SURE IT WAS
JUST THE RADIO.

25:16.427 --> 25:17.690
-WHAT IF IT WASN'T?

25:17.820 --> 25:18.778
-THE COAST GUARD
WILL LET US KNOW.

25:20.649 --> 25:22.172
-THAT'S IT, HUH?
YOU BUSTED A NUDE BEACH.

25:22.303 --> 25:24.044
-YEAH.

25:24.174 --> 25:25.872
-FOR NOW. I'M SURE HOWARD
AND HIS FRIENDS WILL BE BACK.

25:26.002 --> 25:27.787
-YEAH, YOU KNOW, WE SHOULD
FENCE OFF THE TOP OF THAT CLIFF.

25:27.917 --> 25:29.963
-I ALREADY TRIED THAT,
THEY KEEP TEARING IT DOWN.

25:30.093 --> 25:31.355
WE DON'T HAVE ENOUGH
GUARDS TO GUARD IT.

25:31.486 --> 25:33.357
-I'LL PATROL UP THERE.

25:33.488 --> 25:35.708
-JUST IN CASE THEY COME
BACK AGAIN, YOU KNOW?

25:35.838 --> 25:37.361
-YEAH, RIGHT,
THAT'LL BE GREAT PR

25:37.492 --> 25:39.712
FOR OUR JUNIOR LIFEGUARDS,
NUDE BEACH PATROL.

25:39.842 --> 25:41.409
-VOICEOVER:
BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS,

25:41.540 --> 25:42.802
THIS IS COAST GUARD
CUTTER POINT CLARKE, OVER.

25:42.932 --> 25:44.455
-KMF 295.

25:44.586 --> 25:47.328
-ROGER, KMF 295, WE'RE
EN ROUTE TO DIVE BOAT'S

25:47.458 --> 25:48.808
LAST KNOWN POSITION
TO COMMENCE SEARCHING.

25:48.938 --> 25:50.418
WE'LL KEEP YOU ADVISED, OUT.

25:50.549 --> 25:51.941
-THERE'S YOUR CALL,
THEY'RE ALL OVER IT.

25:52.072 --> 25:52.899
SEE YOU, GUYS.

25:56.163 --> 25:59.253
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

25:59.383 --> 26:00.950
-OH, THIS IS A NIGHTMARE.

26:01.647 --> 26:03.605
MY TANK'S AT THE
BOTTOM OF THE OCEAN.

26:04.388 --> 26:06.826
THE TERRORIST MIGHT BE POISONING
THE CITY'S WATER SUPPLY

26:07.478 --> 26:09.263
AND WE'RE TRYING
TO SWIM 20 MILES.

26:10.612 --> 26:14.268
-GUYS, I CAN'T, I CAN'T
SWIM ANY MORE. MY LEG.

26:14.964 --> 26:16.836
-CAROLINE, YOU HAVE A LOT
LEFT INSIDE OF YOU, COME ON.

26:16.966 --> 26:19.316
-NO, I'M TELLING YOU,
I CAN'T.

26:23.146 --> 26:24.278
-COME ON.

26:33.243 --> 26:35.115
-CAROLINE, TAKE MY FINS.

26:35.811 --> 26:37.639
-NO, SAM, YOU NEED THEM.

26:38.858 --> 26:42.209
-SAM, KEEP THEM ON.
CAROLINE, JUST FLOAT, OKAY?

26:42.339 --> 26:43.340
WE'LL SUPPORT YOU.

26:45.647 --> 26:47.823
-ALL RIGHT, HOBESTER,
YOU THE MAN, YOU THE MAN!

26:47.954 --> 26:50.347
[CHEERING]

26:51.218 --> 26:53.612
ALL RIGHT, HOBESTER,
YEAH, YEAH, GO.

26:53.742 --> 26:56.527
-JENNY: YEAH, GO, HOBIE!

26:56.658 --> 26:58.399
[CHEERING]

27:06.929 --> 27:09.584
-HEY, JUMP THE WAKE,
COME ON, JUMP IT!

27:10.367 --> 27:11.804
-JENNY: COME ON!

27:11.934 --> 27:13.414
-JUMP THE WAKE!

27:13.544 --> 27:16.504
[CHEERING]

27:16.635 --> 27:17.679
WHOO!

27:20.334 --> 27:21.814
-HE'S DOWN.

27:21.944 --> 27:22.902
-OKAY, I'M ON IT.

27:31.824 --> 27:33.826
-I'VE GOT TO GET
BACK TO THE BEACH.

27:34.348 --> 27:36.263
ALL THIS PAPERWORK,
I'M REALLY OUT OF SHAPE.

27:41.137 --> 27:42.399
-LOOK, YOU GUYS.

27:43.270 --> 27:44.358
-CAROLINE: IT'S THE CUTTER.

27:45.751 --> 27:46.577
-HELP!

27:46.708 --> 27:49.058
-HEY! OVER HERE!

27:49.189 --> 27:50.538
-OVER HERE!

27:51.495 --> 27:52.932
-HELP!

27:56.196 --> 27:58.241
-I NEED TO TALK TO BAYWATCH
HEADQUARTERS RIGHT AWAY.

27:58.372 --> 27:59.460
CAN I USE YOUR
SHIP'S COMMUNICATION?

27:59.590 --> 28:00.504
-SURE, FOLLOW ME.

28:07.337 --> 28:08.382
-YOU GOT IT.

28:12.734 --> 28:14.562
-I NEED BAYWATCH
HEADQUARTERS RIGHT AWAY.

28:26.748 --> 28:28.315
-THAT WAS A PRETTY
GOOD RUN, GUYS.

28:28.924 --> 28:30.273
I ATE IT OUT THERE, THOUGH.

28:30.404 --> 28:31.971
-YOU WERE AWESOME.

28:32.101 --> 28:33.712
HEY, I JUST SAW SAM'S
DIVE BOAT, WHAT DO YOU SAY

28:33.842 --> 28:35.278
WE CATCH UP TO HER
AND SURPRISE HER.

28:35.409 --> 28:36.540
-LET'S GO.
-MITCH: ALL RIGHT.

28:40.153 --> 28:42.503
-THAT'S RIGHT, TELL THEM
TO ALERT EVERY RESERVOIR

28:42.633 --> 28:44.592
AND WATER TREATMENT PLANT TO
BE ON THE LOOK OUT FOR HIM.

28:45.245 --> 28:48.509
HE'S SIX FEET TALL, BLUE EYES,
HE'S GOT A MILITARY HAIRCUT

28:48.639 --> 28:50.946
AND HE'S WEARING A FLIGHT SUIT
WITH THE NAME QUINLIN ON IT.

28:57.126 --> 29:01.217
-THAT'S STRANGE, IT'S THEIR
BOAT, BUT I DON'T SEE THEM.

29:01.348 --> 29:03.002
JUST SOME GUY DIVING OFF.

29:04.917 --> 29:06.309
WANNA DRIVE FOR A SECOND?

29:06.440 --> 29:07.310
-HOBIE:
YEAH, SURE, NO PROBLEM.

29:07.441 --> 29:08.311
-MITCH: YOU GOT IT?

29:16.493 --> 29:18.191
WHAT IS THAT,
SOMETHING IN HIS HAND.

29:18.321 --> 29:19.801
WHAT IS HE HOLDING?

29:20.410 --> 29:21.672
ALL RIGHT, GET ME OVER THERE.

29:21.803 --> 29:22.935
-LET'S GO.

29:34.773 --> 29:37.384
-MITCH: KMF 295
FROM MITCH BUCHANNON.

29:38.037 --> 29:39.255
-MAN: IT'S YOUR
HEADQUARTERS CALLING BACK.

29:39.386 --> 29:40.822
-THIS IS SAMANTHA THOMAS.

29:40.953 --> 29:42.215
-SAM, I'M GOING TO PATCH
YOU THROUGH TO MITCH.

29:45.348 --> 29:47.960
-HEY, SAM, I JUST SAW
SOME GUY DIVE OFF YOUR BOAT

29:48.090 --> 29:49.004
IN SCUBA GEAR.

29:49.135 --> 29:50.136
-MITCH, WHERE ARE YOU?

29:50.266 --> 29:51.964
-OUT WAKEBOARDING WITH HOBIE.

29:52.094 --> 29:53.487
-EXACTLY WHERE ARE YOU?

29:53.617 --> 29:56.272
-I'M RIGHT NEAR THE
HOOD DESALINATION PLANT.

29:56.403 --> 29:58.927
-MITCH, LISTEN TO ME,
THE DIVER HAS A CANISTER

29:59.058 --> 30:00.668
OF CHOLERA BACTERIA.

30:00.799 --> 30:02.757
HE'S PLANNING ON CONTAMINATING
THE CITY'S WATER SUPPLY.

30:02.888 --> 30:05.412
NOW THERE'S A DISABLE
CODE ON THE CANISTER.

30:05.542 --> 30:08.197
IT'S 099 A 247.

30:08.328 --> 30:10.765
099 A 247.

30:10.896 --> 30:12.811
[BEEPING]

30:25.345 --> 30:26.607
-WHO IS HE?

30:26.737 --> 30:30.567
-I DON'T KNOW.
TERRORIST, SOME NUT.

30:31.220 --> 30:32.352
ALL I KNOW IS THAT
WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME,

30:32.482 --> 30:33.701
I GOTTA STOP THIS GUY.

30:33.832 --> 30:34.745
-REMEMBER THE
CODE SAM GAVE YOU?

30:34.876 --> 30:37.836
-099.
-A 247.

30:37.966 --> 30:40.273
-099 A 247. I GOT IT.

30:41.404 --> 30:43.276
SHE SAID THERE'S ABOUT
TWO MINUTES LEFT,

30:43.406 --> 30:45.539
BUT SHE DOESN'T KNOW IF YOU
CAN DISARM IT UNDER WATER.

30:45.669 --> 30:47.062
-ALL RIGHT, YOU STAY ON BOARD.

30:53.677 --> 30:55.157
-WE NEED TO SHUT
DOWN ALL OPERATION

30:55.288 --> 30:57.420
AT THE HOOD DESALINATION
PLANT IMMEDIATELY.

30:57.551 --> 30:59.770
THE POLICE AND HAZMAT
UNIT ARE ON THEIR WAY.

31:05.689 --> 31:08.344
[BEEPING]

31:48.471 --> 31:50.909
[BEEPING]

32:14.323 --> 32:16.543
[SIRENS BLARING]

32:39.696 --> 32:41.046
-MAN: DOOR'S UP FRONT.

33:14.470 --> 33:15.689
-MITCH: ALL RIGHT,
TAKE HIM, TAKE HIM.

33:15.819 --> 33:17.212
GET EVERYBODY
OUT OF THE WATER.

33:22.478 --> 33:24.132
-MAN:
ALL RIGHT, PULL HIM UP!

33:25.525 --> 33:26.656
-PULL AWAY!

33:27.396 --> 33:29.137
[BEEPING]

33:43.195 --> 33:44.718
-GET READY, YOU GUYS.

33:52.160 --> 33:54.075
-MITCH: EVERYTHING'S
CLEAR, GUYS, IT'S ALL RIGHT.

34:07.175 --> 34:10.483
-I AM SO HOT, DO WE HAVE
TO WEAR ALL OF THESE CLOTHES?

34:10.612 --> 34:12.353
-WE WANNA SHOW THEM
HOW ABSURD IT IS

34:12.485 --> 34:14.007
TO COVER OUR BODIES
AT THE BEACH.

34:14.139 --> 34:16.097
AT THE RIGHT TIME,
WE STRIP DOWN

34:16.228 --> 34:17.577
AND WE DRIVE HOME OUR POINT.

34:18.273 --> 34:20.406
-WOULDN'T IT HAVE BEEN
BETTER TO INVITE THE PRESS?

34:20.536 --> 34:22.364
-NO, THIS WAY,
WE CAN VIDEO EVERYTHING

34:22.495 --> 34:24.279
WITHOUT NETWORK CENSORSHIP
AND THEN SELL IT

34:24.409 --> 34:26.107
TO THE HIGHEST BIDDER.
-OH...

34:27.543 --> 34:29.284
-WHAT IF THE LIFEGUARDS
DON'T SHOW UP?

34:29.415 --> 34:31.591
-DON'T WORRY, THEIR BOATS
WILL BE ALONG SOONER OR LATER.

34:32.157 --> 34:35.333
-HI, I'M SORRY, BUT YOU'RE
NOT ALLOWED DOWN THIS CLIFF.

34:35.464 --> 34:37.379
-STEP ASIDE, SON.

34:37.510 --> 34:39.425
-SIR, I'M SORRY, I CAN'T
LET YOU DOWN THIS WAY.

34:39.554 --> 34:41.601
-HOW ARE WE SUPPOSED
TO GET TO THE BEACH?

34:41.731 --> 34:43.342
-YOU CAN SWIM IN FROM A BOAT.

34:45.300 --> 34:48.216
HEY, YOU'RE NOT THE
NUDISTS, ARE YOU?

34:48.347 --> 34:52.002
-BINGO! AND WHO ARE YOU?
SOMEONE WHO LIKES TO WATCH?

34:52.132 --> 34:55.179
-NO, NO. I'M A
JUNIOR LIFEGUARD.

34:55.310 --> 34:58.357
-HEY, A JUNIOR
LIFEGUARD. FABULOUS.

34:58.487 --> 35:01.882
YOU WERE PUT HERE TO PREVENT
OUR LEGAL ACCESS TO THE BEACH?

35:02.012 --> 35:05.755
-NO, NOT REALLY. KIND
OF VOLUNTEERED ACTUALLY.

35:06.800 --> 35:09.063
-SO, YOU HAVE NO OFFICIAL
AUTHORITY TO STOP US.

35:10.630 --> 35:12.414
-LIKE I SAID, SON,
STEP ASIDE.

35:12.936 --> 35:13.850
COME ON.

35:22.990 --> 35:25.123
-LOOK, THIS CLIFF
IS REALLY DANGEROUS.

35:25.253 --> 35:26.994
A LOT OF PEOPLE HAVE
FALLEN AND BEEN HURT.

35:27.125 --> 35:29.301
-GIRL: WE WON'T
FALL, DON'T WORRY.

35:29.431 --> 35:31.172
WHY DON'T YOU COME
DOWN AND JOIN US?

35:31.694 --> 35:32.869
-NO, I COULDN'T.

35:37.700 --> 35:38.701
-HERE WE GO, AGAIN.

35:40.355 --> 35:42.662
-NO WAY, I'M NOT GETTING
LEFT BEHIND THIS TIME.

35:46.666 --> 35:47.536
-CAREFUL.

35:50.713 --> 35:52.150
-HERE THEY COME NOW.
KEEP TAPING.

35:54.195 --> 35:57.894
OKAY, AS YOU CAN SEE, THE
LIFEGUARDS ONCE AGAIN,

35:58.025 --> 36:02.725
ARE ON THEIR WAY TO TRY AND
SUPPRESS OUR FREEDOM OF--

36:04.814 --> 36:06.251
[SCREAMING]

36:08.209 --> 36:09.732
-HELP!

36:09.863 --> 36:10.951
-HOLD ON!

36:11.691 --> 36:12.779
-HOWARD: HELP!

36:25.400 --> 36:28.621
HURRY! HURRY THE
BRANCH IS GONNA GO!

36:28.751 --> 36:29.796
HURRY!

36:36.846 --> 36:37.804
HURRY UP!

36:42.156 --> 36:43.723
HELP!

36:56.953 --> 36:59.260
HURRY, PLEASE, HURRY!

37:14.057 --> 37:16.103
HURRY! HELP ME!

37:20.281 --> 37:21.543
-YOU GOT IT.

37:27.636 --> 37:30.465
-HOWARD: OH, NO, I'M
GONNA FALL, I'M GONNA FALL!

37:39.779 --> 37:40.954
-GRAB MY WAIST.

37:50.572 --> 37:51.486
GOT IT?

37:53.053 --> 37:55.055
-HOWARD: THROW
ME A LINE, HURRY!

38:01.104 --> 38:04.586
HELP! HELP, I'M SLIPPING!

38:09.548 --> 38:12.768
HELP, HELP! COME ON!

38:16.642 --> 38:20.689
HURRY! PLEASE HELP ME!

38:30.743 --> 38:31.961
GRAB MY FEET!

38:37.358 --> 38:38.620
-CODY: OKAY, OKAY,
WE GOT YOU.

38:43.451 --> 38:45.627
I HOPE WE'RE NOT IMPEDING
YOUR CIVIL RIGHTS.

38:45.758 --> 38:48.108
-NO, NO, NO, NO. PLEASE
JUST GET ME TO SAFETY.

39:00.729 --> 39:01.861
-GRAB THE ROPE!

39:21.271 --> 39:22.229
-NEWMIE:
YOU GOT HIM, MANNY?

39:22.360 --> 39:23.273
-YEAH.

39:42.597 --> 39:44.904
[TALKING OVER ONE ANOTHER]

39:48.995 --> 39:51.650
-LOOKS LIKE YOU GOT ANOTHER
INCIDENT REPORT TO FILE, MANNY.

39:53.129 --> 39:55.175
EXCEPT THIS TIME
YOU GET TO FILL IT OUT.

39:56.263 --> 39:57.917
-REALLY?

39:58.047 --> 40:00.528
-HEY, TWO LIVES. DOUBT THAT
ANYONE SAVED MORE TODAY.

40:08.014 --> 40:08.884
-GET DOWN ON THE HOOD.

40:09.015 --> 40:10.146
HANDS BEHIND YOUR BACK.

40:11.583 --> 40:14.020
[CHATTERING]

40:34.519 --> 40:35.781
-WAY TO GO, DAD.

40:35.911 --> 40:36.869
YOU WERE AWESOME.

40:40.612 --> 40:41.961
-MOVE IT.

40:42.701 --> 40:44.311
JUST KEEP WALKING.

40:52.798 --> 40:54.364
-MAN: BRING HIM IN
AND PUT HIM BACK.

40:55.322 --> 40:56.279
-WATCH YOUR HEAD.

41:01.371 --> 41:02.460
-ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

41:04.592 --> 41:06.072
-NEVER HAD A BETTER DAY.

41:15.647 --> 41:17.475
[CLOSING THEME PLAYING]
